Parallel Coordinates Charts

Use a parallel coordinates chart when you have multiple measures and a single grouping. Parallel coordinate charts are useful for displaying how data elements in a grouping stack up against each other.

Create a Parallel Coordinates Chart

In the lens, click  and then select the Parallel Coordinates chart type.
In the Node Measures field, add the measures you're interested in.
To compare product pricing, add average unit cost, discount, shipping cost, and profit.
In the Lines field, add the dimension that youâ€™d like to group the data by. Each group gets its own line.

The parallel coordinates chart shows that higher discounts aren't adding up to higher profits.

To change the chart display, click  and set the chart properties in the Formatting panel. For example, indicate whether to show every measure title in the chart.
